.TH "page_counter_try_charge" 9 "page_counter_try_charge" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
page_counter_try_charge \- try to hierarchically charge pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" page_counter_try_charge
.BI "(struct page_counter *counter "  ","
.BI "unsigned long nr_pages "  ","
.BI "struct page_counter **fail "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "counter" 12
counter
.IP "nr_pages" 12
number of pages to charge
.IP "fail" 12
points first counter to hit its limit, if any
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns true on success, or false and \fIfail\fP if the counter or one
of its ancestors has hit its configured limit.
